To create a sparking background in HTML that looks like the night sky, you can use the following code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>Sparkling Night Sky</title>
	<style type="text/css">
		body {
			background-color: #000046;
			background-image: url('https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2015/01/01/22/15/galaxy-586344_960_720.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
			background-position: center center;
			background-repeat: no-repeat;
			background-attachment: fixed;
		}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<!-- Content goes here -->
</body>
</html>
```

In the code, the `background-color` property sets the background color to a dark blue shade. The `background-image` property adds an image of the night sky. The `background-size` property scales the image to fill the screen. The `background-position` property centers the image both horizontally and vertically. The `background-repeat` property ensures that the image is not repeated. Finally, the `background-attachment` property makes sure that the background image does not scroll with the page.
